One year after his demise, actor Yul Edochie has said he misses the founder of Synagogue Church of All Nations (SCOAN) Prophet Temitope Babatunde Joshua aka TB Joshua. On Sunday, June 5, followers thronged SCOAN in Ikotun, Lagos to celebrate the legacies of the preacher. The event, also attended by diverse foreign nationals, was filled with nostalgia of glamorous and spirit-filled worship in the people, as it was during the days of the prophet. The service with theme: “Celebrating the Life and Legacy of Prophet TB Joshua” featured some Nigerian celebrities, including popular comedian Ali Baba, K C Brown and Tee Mac, who entertained people.   Wife sweetest thing that can never cause me diabetes –…     Davido reportedly eyes Lori Harvey     I’m ready for an arranged marriage – Latsha…   Many foreign gospel ministers who also attended the service included Pastor Freyle from Colombia, Pastor William Ghaltas from Bethlehem, Pastor Obispo Elvis from the Dominican Republic and Bishop Trevor Williamson and wife from Bahamas. Others included Pastor Bernard Mulder of South Africa and Bishop Steven Ogedengbe from Nigeria. Taking to his Instagram page, the actor, shared the prophet’s photo noting how unbelievable his passing still feels to him. “I still can’t believe you’re gone. It’s one year already. God knows best. I miss you. I’ll continue to celebrate your life on earth. “Rest well Sir. SNR. PROPHET T.B JOSHUA,” Yul Edochie wrote.